properties.Title: Special Weather Statement In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Risk of freezing rain this morning A frontal system will track across the southern BC interior today. Flurries are expected this morning. The warm air aloft combined with near or below zero temperatures at the surface will result in a risk of freezing rain. The flurries with the risk of freezing rain will change to rain showers this afternoon as temperatures rise above zero. Surfaces such as highways, road, walkways and parking lots may become icy and slippery. Take extra caution when walking or driving in affected areas. ### Weather in the mountains can change suddenly resulting in hazardous driving conditions. Road conditions are available at www.drivebc.ca. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to BCstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #BCStorm.
Expires: 2019-11-24T01:59:47-00:00

properties.Title: Update: High Water Advisory Alert Is Being Issued For The Roseau River From Gardenton To Stuartburn
properties.Summary:
Description: Update: This is a Manitoba Emergency Alert. Manitoba Infrastructure's Hydrologic Forecast Centre has issued a High Water Advisory for the Roseau River from Gardenton to Stuartburn due to expected high flows. If you are in the affected area, be watchful of local waterways as flooding is likely to occur. Do not attempt to cross fast flowing waters or waters of unknown depth. Avoid flooded areas. Follow all directions by the local authorities. Listen for updates and take all necessary precautions to stay safe. Up-to-date information is available at www.gov.mb.ca/flooding and www.manitoba511.ca or stay tuned to local media.
Expires: 2019-11-24T11:30:00-06:00

properties.Title: Snowfall Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Snowfall with total amounts of 10 to 15 cm is expected. Snow is expected to develop over northern sections of Banff National Park along Highway 93 from Sunwapta Pass to the village of Lake Louise this evening. Total snowfall amounts will be 10 centimetres by Sunday morning. The townsite of Banff itself is likely to only receive 2 centimetres from this weather system. ### Rapidly accumulating snow could make travel difficult over some locations. Visibility may be suddenly reduced at times in heavy snow. Snowfall warnings are issued when significant snowfall is expected. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to ABstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #ABStorm.

properties.Title: Snowfall Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Snowfall with total amounts of 20 to 30 cm is expected. Snow at times heavy is expected over the Highlands of Inverness and Victoria Counties today, persisting until after midnight tonight. Accumulations of up to 30 centimetres are forecast, although locally greater amounts are possible over the highest terrain. Wet snow with lesser accumulations near 5 to 10 centimetres is expected over lower elevations, since temperatures are forecast to remain slightly above freezing. Strong westerly winds will combine with the snow to give poor visibility at times over the higher terrain this afternoon and evening. Motorists are advised to prepare for winter driving conditions. ### Visibility may be suddenly reduced at times in heavy snow. Rapidly accumulating snow will make travel difficult. Snowfall warnings are issued when significant snowfall is expected. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NSstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NSStorm.
